Stability and uniqueness of models
Consider an \(\mathrm{AR}(1)\) model: we can expand the recursive formula as: \[
\begin{align}
x_t =& \phi x_{t-1}+w_t = \phi(\phi x_{t-2}+w_{t-1}) + w_t \\
=& \sum_{j=0}^{+\infty}\phi^j w_{t-j}
\end{align}
\] It is therefore clear that the time series \(x_t\) is stable only if \(|\phi|&lt;1\)
In the general case of the \(\mathrm{AR}(p)\) model, the stability condition is: \[
\left|\sum_{i=1}^p \phi_i\right| &lt; 1 \label{eq:ARstab}
\] An unstable AR model is also called anti-causal, because it can be shown that to be stabilized it requires knowledge of future observations

Querying a time range in MongoDB


{
  "_id": {
    "$oid": "698afb51c3b4084d840b9c85"
  },
  "timestamp": {
    "$date": "2026-02-10T09:33:05.344Z"
  },
  "measure": {
    "back_bend": -0.5168184041976929,
    "back_flex": -1.20260488986969,
    "back_rot": 1.749389410018921,
    "cervical_flex": 17.3467960357666,
    "horiz_reach_left": 0.20939064025878906,
    "horiz_reach_right": 0.20467370748519897,
    "hostname": "nuc3",
    "stability_margin": 0.11027171462774277,
    "timecode": 37985.2,
    "vert_reach_left": 14.016213417053223,
    "vert_reach_right": 10.769205093383789
  }
}

The standard pattern is:

inclusive lower bound: $gte
exclusive upper bound: $lt

This avoids overlap when adjacent windows are queried one after another
db.measurements.find({
  timestamp: {
    $gte: ISODate("2026-02-10T08:00:00.000Z"),
    $lt:  ISODate("2026-02-10T10:00:00.000Z")
  }
}).sort({ timestamp: 1 })




For performance, a range query on timestamp should be supported by an index on the same field, or by a compound index such as { machine_id: 1, timestamp: 1 }.

MongoDB query in JavaScript
const t0 = ISODate("2026-03-09T08:00:00.000Z");
const t1 = ISODate("2026-03-09T09:00:00.000Z");

db.measurements.find(
  {
    machine_id: "M01",
    timestamp: { $gte: t0, $lt: t1 }
  },
  {
    _id: 0,
    machine_id: 1,
    timestamp: 1,
    temperature: 1,
    vibration: 1
  }
).sort({ timestamp: 1 });

MongoDB query in R
library(mongolite)
library(glue)
m &lt;- mongo(collection = "measurements", db = "plant", url = "mongodb://localhost:27017")
t0 &lt;- "2026-03-09T08:00:00.000Z"
t1 &lt;- "2026-03-09T09:00:00.000Z"
query &lt;- glue(
'{{
  "machine_id": "M01",
  "timestamp": {{
    "$gte": {{"$date": "{t0}"}},
    "$lt":  {{"$date": "{t1}"}}
  }}
}}'
)
fields &lt;- '{"_id": 0, "machine_id": 1,
            "timestamp": 1, "temperature": 1,
            "vibration": 1}'
df &lt;- m$find(query = query, fields = fields, sort = '{"timestamp": 1}')
